articles.title: L+600 and counting: ESA astronaut to be 600th person in space - collectSPACE.com
articles.description: A German astronaut is set to become the 600th person to enter space and he will do so flying with a U.S. astronaut who once came close to being number 500. Matthias Maurer with the European Space Agency will be the sexcentenarian space traveler.
articles.content:

articles.title: 150 people arrested, over $31M seized in international drug trafficking sting: Department of Justice - Fox News
articles.description: U.S. and European law enforcement officials have arrested 150 people and seized more than $31 million in an international drug trafficking investigation stemming from sales on the darknet, the Justice Department announced on Tuesday.
